{"_note":"John Deere OEM parts catalog for Marion, harvested LIVE from sealsonline.com (Fluidseal AB / flabed storefront) on 2026-06-18. This is the oem-parts layer: an OEM (John Deere) whose relationship to Fluidseal is part-number -> part-number (plus that part's own detail), NOT profile -> profile. Each entry is a real Fluidseal stock part with a verified leaf URL. Marion uses this to answer 'what's the Fluidseal equivalent of John Deere <number>' with a confirmed part number, and the quote tool (quote.html) uses it to resolve OEM references to Fluidseal part numbers.","oem":"John Deere","source":"https://www.sealsonline.com/en/flabed/categories/oem-kits-parts/mobile-equipment-seal-kits/john-deere/john-deere-parts","source_type":"live-website","harvested":"2026-06-18","version":"1.0","count":82,"part_number_convention":{"rule":"Fluidseal John Deere part number = 'RJD-' + the John Deere reference/OEM number, preserving the OEM's own letter prefix. Observed prefixes: T, AT, R, TH, H, U, RE, AH, YZ, FYB, 4S, and bare-numeric (e.g. 4487585). So OEM T108050 -> RJD-T108050; OEM AT131420 -> RJD-AT131420.","exceptions":["Filler Ring series uses a Fluidseal INTERNAL sizing code 'RJD-TD' + inside-diameter-in-mm (RJD-TD45 = 45mm ID, RJD-TD120 = 120mm ID), NOT an OEM number. These carry oem_ref=null.","RJD-FR120 and RJD-TDKIT are Fluidseal house/kit codes, not OEM numbers (oem_ref=null)."],"url_slug_rule":"lowercase the part number and hyphen-split each letter-run from each digit-run: RJD-T108050 -> rjd-t-108050; RJD-AT131420 -> rjd-at-131420; RJD-4S00225 -> rjd-4-s-00225; bare-numeric stays whole (RJD-4487585 -> rjd-4487585); all-letter tails stay whole (RJD-TDKIT -> rjd-tdkit). URL = <john-deere-parts>/<category-slug>/<part-slug>."},"DATA_INTEGRITY_NOTE":{"resolved":"The Serge Construction estimate showed RJD-TD187116 for OEM T187116; David confirmed that was a transcription slip — the correct number is RJD-T187116. The convention is uniform: RJD- + the full OEM reference 